CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, National edition, March 27, 1948, pg. 13, reads: "Alpha's Pittsburgh Home - Recently purchased by Pittsburgh Alpha Phi Alpha men, the former Coleman Home for Boys on Centre Avenue will house the activities of the Alpha Omicron Lambda Chapters and Omicron chapters. The house held its formal opening exercises Sunday. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Alpha Phi Alpha fraternity house, formally Coleman Home for Boys, 3046 Centre Avenue, Hill District
